Modjadji Manganye sustained third degree burns to her body after mistakenly getting into the tub at the Elim Hospital. JOHANNESBURG - Family members of an 83-year-old woman who died after getting into a hot bath tub at a hospital in Limpopo say they're relieved they were able to bury their loved one in a dignified manner.Modjadji Manganye sustained third degree burns to her body after mistakenly getting into the tub at the Elim Hospital.The family says it plans to pursue legal actions against the Health Department to hold them accountable for negligence.Manganye's grandson Jabu Manganye says: We will sit down to discuss what to do next. I can tell you legal action will be taken. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)